'''Azam Taleghani''' (in Persian:<U+0627><U+0639><U+0638><U+0645> <U+0637><U+0627><U+0644><U+0642><U+0627><U+0646><U+06CC>) is an [[Iran]]ian [[politician]] and [[journalist]], born in 1944, is the head of the Society of Islamic Revolution Women of Iran,<ref name=payvand>[http://www.payvand.com/news/03/aug/1071.html Iran: Sit-in by Azam Taleghani in front of Evin prison]</ref> editor of ''Payam Hajar'' Weekly, and a former member of the [[Iranian parliament]].<ref name=Farokhzad><U+0641><U+0631><U+062E><U+200C><U+0632><U+0627><U+062F><U+060C> <U+067E><U+0648><U+0631><U+0627><U+0646> ([[Pooran Farrokhzad]]). <U+06A9><U+0627><U+0631><U+0646><U+0645><U+0627><U+06CC> <U+0632><U+0646><U+0627><U+0646> <U+06A9><U+0627><U+0631><U+0627><U+06CC> <U+0627><U+06CC><U+0631><U+0627><U+0646> (<U+0627><U+0632> <U+062F><U+06CC><U+0631><U+0648><U+0632> <U+062A><U+0627> <U+0627><U+0645><U+0631><U+0648><U+0632>). <U+062A><U+0647><U+0631><U+0627><U+0646>: <U+0646><U+0634><U+0631> <U+0642><U+0637><U+0631><U+0647><U+060C> <U+06F1><U+06F3><U+06F8><U+06F1><U+060C> ISBN 9643411168<U+060C> <U+200F>533.</ref> 

Born in Iran, Taleghani is the daughter of Ayatollah [[Mahmoud Taleghani]]. She served time in prison during the [[Pahlavi regime]].<ref>[http://radiozamaaneh.com/hamayesh/2007/12/post_21.html <U+0647><U+0645><U+0627><U+06CC><U+0634> <U+06CC><U+06A9><U+0635><U+062F><U+0645><U+06CC><U+0646> <U+0633><U+0627><U+0644> <U+062A><U+0648><U+0644><U+062F> <U+0645><U+0647><U+0646><U+062F><U+0633> <U+0628><U+0627><U+0632><U+0631><U+06AF><U+0627><U+0646>]</ref> After the [[Iranian Revolution]] she was a member of the [[Iranian parliament]], founded "Jame'e Zanan Mosalman" (Society of Muslim women), and published ''Payam e Hajar'' Weekly, an Islamic journal about women and [[women's rights]].<ref name="Farokhzad"/> In 2003 she protested against the death of [[Zahra Kazemi]].<ref name="payvand"/><ref>[http://www.zanan.co.ir/news/000133.html <U+062A><U+062D><U+0635><U+0646> <U+0627><U+0639><U+0638><U+0645> <U+0637><U+0627><U+0644><U+0642><U+0627><U+0646><U+06CC> <U+062F><U+0631> <U+0645><U+0642><U+0627><U+0628><U+0644> <U+0632><U+0646><U+062F><U+0627><U+0646> <U+0627><U+0648><U+06CC><U+0646>]</ref> Both in 2001 and 2009, Taleghani submitted her candidacy for Iran's presidential elections, but, like all women's candidacies, her candidacy was rejected by Iran's [[Guardian Council]] .<ref>[http://irwomen.net/spip.php?article4456 <U+06AF><U+0641><U+062A><U+06AF><U+0648><U+06CC> <U+062E><U+0628><U+0631><U+0646><U+06AF><U+0627><U+0631><U+0627><U+0646> <U+062A><U+0631><U+06A9> <U+0628><U+0627> <U+0627><U+0639><U+0638><U+0645> <U+0637><U+0627><U+0644><U+0642><U+0627><U+0646><U+06CC>]</ref><ref>[http://www.entekhabnews.com/portal/index.php?news=2110 <U+0627><U+0639><U+0638><U+0645> <U+0637><U+0627><U+0644><U+0642><U+0627><U+0646><U+06CC> <U+06A9><U+0627><U+0646><U+062F><U+06CC><U+062F><U+0627><U+06CC> <U+062C><U+062F><U+06CC><U+062F> <U+0631><U+06CC><U+0627><U+0633><U+062A> <U+062C><U+0645><U+0647><U+0648><U+0631><U+06CC>]</ref>

